# Tools

#Tools


The room allows you to download task files which includes the tools that maybe necessary for conducting the Penetration Test. But, here I have listed all the tools that I used and the url links or commands to download them. 

Tools will be categorized as per 

Tool name : function: source: miscellaneous information

•	nmap: reconnaissance: https://nmap.org/ : generally in built in Kali Linux

•	Binaries of - to be planted and used from compromised hosts without dependencies

o	socat: forking traffic: https://github.com/aledbf/socat-static-binary 
o	nmap: recon from compromised host: https://github.com/opsec-infosec/nmap-static-binaries
o	chisel: pivoting through internal network hosts: https://github.com/jpillora/chisel: different scripts for Linux and Windows target host

•	shuttle: Pivoting:https://github.com/sshuttle/sshuttle: subnet wide tunnel, target host must be Linux OS

•	evil-winrm: Exploitation, shell: only for windows target host

•	netcat: listener : https://nmap.org/download.html#linux-rpm: (used here for catching reverse shells)

•	Crackstation: online hash cracker: https://crackstation.net/

•	Invoke-Portscan.ps1: Enumeration for Windows: https://www.powershellgallery.com/packages/NetworkScan/0.0.1/Content/Invoke-PortScan.ps1

•	exiftool: editing metadata: https://exiftool.org/install.html: command line tool for editing metadata within variety of formats like images, audio and video

•	Php obfuscator: obfuscator for Php code: https://github.com/mnestorov/php-obfuscator

•	mcs - mono: compiler for C# programming language: 

•	smbserver.py - enables smb share

•	secretsdump.py - post exploitation Python script which extracts sensitive credentials and secrets (NTDS.dit, SAM, and .SYSTEM registry hives).
